    • getCustomFunction

      public String getCustomFunction()
      Description copied from interface: ICustomMenuItem
      This function is used to get the function name of a custom item in order to store it in files and databases. Override this method and return a custom function name that you will check to see if an item is the item you are looking for. Then load that item and add it to the page.
      Returns:
      Item classes custom function name

    • read

      public static ExampleCustomUpgradeItem read(Map<String,Object> configMap, UpgradeItem base)
      This is used to read the item from the config file. It takes in a Map object and a base shop item. Data is not flattened in the config file, so keys will match the write function, with sub keys (and their corresponding maps) for nested data.
      Parameters:
      configMap - The Map object that contains the data for this event.
      base - The base item that contains the data that is common to all shop items.
      Returns:
      The ExampleCustomUpgradeItem that was read from the config file.

    • readSQL

      public static ExampleCustomUpgradeItem readSQL(Row row, UpgradeItem base)
      This is used to read the item from the SQL database. It takes in a Row object, which is a flattened form of the data in the database. This allows for easy access to the data, key for key basically.
      Parameters:
      row - The Row object that contains the data for this shop item.
      base - The base item that contains the data that is common to all shop items.
      Returns:
      The ExampleCustomUpgradeItem that was read from the database.
